Micryletta inornata
differs from
M. erythropoda
(based on Tarkhnishvili 1994 ;
Poyarkov et al . 2018
) by its smaller snout-vent size in males, SVL 16.8–20.5 mm , N = 3 (vs. SVL up to 30 mm ); tibiotarsal articulation of adpressed limb reaching up to the level of eye (vs. reaching up to the level of posterior edge of tympanum); outer metatarsal tubercle absent (vs. present); webbing between toes absent (vs. rudimentary webbing); dorsum brownish-grey with a silver tinge (vs. grey or beige to saturated ochre or brick-red); dorsum with irregular blackish-brown blotches of variable size (vs. irregular dark spots); flank light brown with blackish-brown spots (vs. dark brown to grey with white patches); and ventral surfaces light reddish-grey without mottling (vs. with mottling).
